==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mousse
<hw>Mousse</hw> <pr>(m⟦oomac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A frozen dessert of a frothy
texture, made of sweetened and flavored whipped cream, sometimes with
the addition of egg yolks and gelatin. Mousse differs from ice cream in
being beaten before -- not during -- the freezing process.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any of a variety of foods whipped to a light
texture; <as>as, a salmon <ex>mousse</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A foam containing special chemicals, used for
styling hair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mousseline</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
